oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Paymaster's office and campsite at Dale Hollow Dam
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Photograph of the paymaster's office at the campsite of Morrison-Knudsen Company contractors. Men are walking in front of building on the left, and a group of men are seen standing to the right of the porch. Snow is covering the roof and the hilltop behind the building.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Camps; Dams; Construction
